ElasticsearchClient(string, AuthorizationHeader)

Creates a client configured to communicate with Elastic Cloud using the provided cloudId.

See the CloudNodePool documentation for more information on how to obtain your Cloud Id.

If you want more control, use the ElasticsearchClient(IElasticsearchClientSettings) constructor and pass an instance of ElasticsearchClientSettings that takes a cloudId in its constructor as well. 

public ElasticsearchClient(string cloudId, AuthorizationHeader credentials)

Parameters

cloudId string

The Cloud ID of an Elastic Cloud deployment.

credentials AuthorizationHeader

The credentials to use for the connection.
